+     * window's sprite 0 via HuSpr3DSet), called from HuSprDisp's own
+     * per-layer loop -- an arbitrary amount of OTHER code can run between
+     * this function's own last vertex and whatever the NEXT real GXBegin
+     * happens to be, and the bridge's generic "auto-close on the next
+     * GXBegin" tolerance has no way to know this function's own primitive
+     * was already, correctly, complete well before that point. Caught
+     * directly (Aurora build): "GXEnd: vertex count mismatch: GXBegin
+     * declared 128 vertices (8B each, 1024B total) but 1075 bytes were
+     * written (134 vertices)" -- extra bytes from whatever ran in the gap
